trend_summary: Built-up area gradually radiates from the south-east core, transforming adjacent farmland into housing estates and light industry. New roads and roundabouts interlink growing hamlets. Woodland edges recede slightly, though small regrowth patches appear north-west. Despite expansion, fields and forest still dominate, giving a medium-density, suburban character overall.
notable_changes: Southeastern town footprint roughly doubles, with noticeable estate infill between images 1 and 5.
New arterial road and feeder streets extend westward, tightening the regional network.
Several forest patches in central corridor cleared and converted to agriculture or housing.
Isolated farm plots subdivided into smaller, regular parcels, indicating intensified cultivation.
Small industrial/commercial structures emerge near main junction in the south-east.
